interfaces.label: IUiSettingsClient
description:
Client-side client that provides access to the advanced settings stored in elasticsearch.
The settings provide control over the behavior of the Kibana application.
For example, a user can specify how to display numeric or date fields.
Users can adjust the settings via Management UI.
{@link IUiSettingsClient}

children.label: get
description:
Gets the value for a specific uiSetting. If this setting has no user-defined value
then the `defaultOverride` parameter is returned (and parsed if setting is of type
"json" or "number). If the parameter is not defined and the key is not registered
by any plugin then an error is thrown, otherwise reads the default value defined by a plugin.
signature: <T = any>(key: string, defaultOverride?: T | undefined) => T

children.label: get$
description:
Gets an observable of the current value for a config key, and all updates to that config

children.label: set
description:
Sets the value for a uiSetting. If the setting is not registered by any plugin
it will be stored as a custom setting. The new value will be synchronously available via
the `get()` method and sent to the server in the background. If the request to the
server fails then a updateErrors$ will be notified and the setting will be
reverted to its value before `set()` was called.

children.label: remove
description:
Removes the user-defined value for a setting, causing it to revert to the default. This
method behaves the same as calling `set(key, null)`, including the synchronization, custom
setting, and error behavior of that method.

children.label: isDeclared
description:
Returns true if the key is a "known" uiSetting, meaning it is either registered

children.label: isDefault
description: Returns true if the setting has no user-defined value or is unknown

children.label: isCustom
description:
Returns true if the setting wasn't registered by any plugin, but was either
added directly via `set()`, or is an unknown setting found in the uiSettings saved
object

children.label: isOverridden
description: Shows whether the uiSettings value set by the user.

misc.label: SavedObjectsImportWarning
SavedObjectsNamespaceType
description:
The namespace type dictates how a saved object can be interacted in relation to namespaces. Each type is mutually exclusive:
 * single (default): This type of saved object is namespace-isolated, e.g., it exists in only one namespace.
 * multiple: This type of saved object is shareable, e.g., it can exist in one or more namespaces.
 * multiple-isolated: This type of saved object is namespace-isolated, e.g., it exists in only one namespace, but object IDs must be
   unique across all namespaces. This is intended to be an intermediate step when objects with a "single" namespace type are being
   converted to a "multiple" namespace type. In other words, objects with a "multiple-isolated" namespace type will be *share-capable*,
   but will not actually be shareable until the namespace type is changed to "multiple".
 * agnostic: This type of saved object is global.

interfaces.label: IUiSettingsClient
description:
Server-side client that provides access to the advanced settings stored in elasticsearch.
The settings provide control over the behavior of the Kibana application.
For example, a user can specify how to display numeric or date fields.
Users can adjust the settings via Management UI.

description:
Describes the set of required and optional properties plugin can define in its
mandatory JSON manifest file.

Identifier of the plugin. Must be a string in camelCase. Part of a plugin public contract.
Other plugins leverage it to access plugin API, navigate to the plugin, etc.

children.label: type

children.label: configPath
description:
Root {@link ConfigPath | configuration path} used by the plugin, defaults
to "id" in snake_case format.

children.label: requiredPlugins

An optional list of the other plugins that **must be** installed and enabled
for this plugin to function properly.

List of plugin ids that this plugin's UI code imports modules from that are
not in `requiredPlugins`.

children.label: optionalPlugins

An optional list of the other plugins that if installed and enabled **may be**
leveraged by this plugin for some additional functionality but otherwise are
not required for this plugin to work properly.

children.label: ui
description:
Specifies whether plugin includes some client/browser specific functionality
that should be included into client bundle via `public/ui_plugin.js` file.

children.label: server
description: Specifies whether plugin includes some server-side specific functionality.

children.label: extraPublicDirs
description:
Specifies directory names that can be imported by other ui-plugins built
using the same instance of the @kbn/optimizer. A temporary measure we plan
to replace with better mechanisms for sharing static code between plugins

Only used for the automatically generated API documentation. Specifying service
folders will cause your plugin API reference to be broken up into sub sections.

interfaces.label: PrebootPlugin
description: The interface that should be returned by a `PluginInitializer` for a `preboot` plugin.

interfaces.label: PrebootServicePreboot
description: Kibana Preboot Service allows to control the boot flow of Kibana. Preboot plugins can use it to hold the boot until certain condition is met.

children.label: isSetupOnHold
description: Indicates whether Kibana is currently on hold and cannot proceed to `setup` yet.

children.label: holdSetupUntilResolved
description:
Registers a `Promise` as a precondition before Kibana can proceed to `setup`. This method can be invoked multiple
times and from multiple `preboot` plugins. Kibana will proceed to `setup` only when all registered `Promises`
instances are resolved, or it will shut down if any of them is rejected.
signature: (reason: string, promise: Promise<{ shouldReloadConfig: boolean; } | undefined>) => void

children.label: reason
description:
A string that explains the reason why this promise should hold `setup`. It's supposed to be a human
readable string that will be recorded in the logs or standard output.

children.label: promise
description: A `Promise` that should resolved before Kibana can proceed to `setup`.

interfaces.label: RequestHandlerContext
description:
Plugin specific context passed to a route handler.

Provides the following clients and services:
   - {@link SavedObjectsClient | savedObjects.client} - Saved Objects client
     which uses the credentials of the incoming request
   - {@link ISavedObjectTypeRegistry | savedObjects.typeRegistry} - Type registry containing
     all the registered types.
   - {@link IScopedClusterClient | elasticsearch.client} - Elasticsearch
     data client which uses the credentials of the incoming request
   - {@link IUiSettingsClient | uiSettings.client} - uiSettings client
     which uses the credentials of the incoming request

interfaces.label: ResolveCapabilitiesOptions
description: Defines a set of additional options for the `resolveCapabilities` method of {@link CapabilitiesStart}.

children.label: useDefaultCapabilities
description: Indicates if capability switchers are supposed to return a default set of capabilities.

children.label: id
description: The ID of this Saved Object, guaranteed to be unique for all objects of the same `type`

children.label: type
description: The type of Saved Object. Each plugin can define it's own custom Saved Object types.

children.label: version
description: An opaque version number which changes on each successful write operation. Can be used for implementing optimistic concurrency control.

children.label: updated_at
description: Timestamp of the last time this document had been updated.

children.label: attributes
description: {@inheritdoc SavedObjectAttributes}

children.label: references
description: {@inheritdoc SavedObjectReference}

children.label: migrationVersion
description: {@inheritdoc SavedObjectsMigrationVersion}

children.label: coreMigrationVersion
description: A semver value that is used when upgrading objects between Kibana versions.

children.label: namespaces
description:
Space(s) that this saved object exists in. This attribute is not used for "global" saved object types which are registered with
`namespaceType: 'agnostic'`.

children.label: originId
description:
The ID of the saved object this originated from. This is set if this object's `id` was regenerated; that can happen during migration
from a legacy single-namespace type, or during import. It is only set during migration or create operations. This is used during import
to ensure that ID regeneration is deterministic, so saved objects will be overwritten if they are imported multiple times into a given
space.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectAttributes
description:
The data for a Saved Object is stored as an object in the `attributes`
property.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectReference
description: A reference to another saved object.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsMigrationVersion
description:
Information about the migrations that have been applied to this SavedObject.
When Kibana starts up, KibanaMigrator detects outdated documents and
migrates them based on this value. For each migration that has been applied,
the plugin's name is used as a key and the latest migration version as the
value.

machine-readable information about the service status. May include status information for underlying features.

description: API for accessing status of Core and this plugin's dependencies as well as for customizing this plugin's status.

children.label: core$
description: Current status for all Core services.

children.label: overall$
description: Overall system status for all of Kibana.

children.label: set
description:
Allows a plugin to specify a custom status dependent on its own criteria.
Completely overrides the default inherited status.

children.label: dependencies$
description:
Current status for all plugins this plugin depends on.
Each key of the `Record` is a plugin id.

children.label: derivedStatus$
description: The status of this plugin as derived from its dependencies.

children.label: isStatusPageAnonymous
description:
Whether or not the status HTTP APIs are available to unauthenticated users when an authentication provider is
present.

interfaces.label: UiSettingsParams
description: UiSettings parameters defined by the plugins.

children.label: name
description: title in the UI

children.label: value
description: default value to fall back to if a user doesn't provide any

children.label: description
description: description provided to a user in UI

children.label: category
description: used to group the configured setting in the UI

children.label: options
description: array of permitted values for this setting

children.label: optionLabels
description: text labels for 'select' type UI element

children.label: requiresPageReload
description: a flag indicating whether new value applying requires page reloading

children.label: readonly
description: a flag indicating that value cannot be changed

children.label: sensitive
description:
a flag indicating that value might contain user sensitive data.
used by telemetry to mask the value of the setting when sent.

children.label: type
description: defines a type of UI element {@link UiSettingsType}

children.label: deprecation
description: optional deprecation information. Used to generate a deprecation warning.

children.label: order
description:
index of the settings within its category (ascending order, smallest will be displayed first).
Used for ordering in the UI.

children.label: metric
description: Metric to track once this property changes

children.label: register
description: Sets settings with default values for the uiSettings.

children.label: asScopedToClient
description:
Creates a {@link IUiSettingsClient} with provided *scoped* saved objects client.

This should only be used in the specific case where the client needs to be accessed
from outside of the scope of a {@link RequestHandler}.

interfaces.label: UnauthorizedErrorHandlerToolkit
description: Toolkit passed to a {@link UnauthorizedErrorHandler} used to generate responses from the handler

children.label: notHandled
description: The handler cannot handle the error, or was not able to authenticate.

children.label: retry
description: The handler was able to authenticate. Will retry the failed request with new auth headers

interfaces.label: UserProvidedValues
description: Describes the values explicitly set by user.
